  <recipe>
    <head>
      <title>Apple Tapioca</title>
      <categories>
        <cat>Desserts</cat>
        <cat>Fruits</cat>
        <cat>Low fat</cat></categories>
      <yield>6</yield></head>
    <ingredients>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Pearl tapioca</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Water</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>6</qty>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Apples; peeled and cored</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/2</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Sugar</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Cinnamon</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty/>
          <unit/></amt>
        <item>Nutmeg</item></ing>
      <ing>
        <amt>
          <qty>1/4</qty>
          <unit>cups</unit></amt>
        <item>Butter</item></ing></ingredients>
    <directions>
      <step>  Soak tapioca according to box and then drain. Bring water to a boil and add
  tapioca.  Boil until clear and thick, stirring often.
  
  Cut apples into eighths and place in a 8x8" casserole. Sprinkle with sugar,
  cinnamon and nutmeg.  Dot with butter.  Pour hot tapioca over all.  Bake
  1/2 hour at 350Ã¸ or until apples are done.
  
